# AquaDock CRM v5 – Core Architecture Rules

- Use Server Components by default for data fetching and Supabase queries.
- All forms must use Zod schemas from `src/lib/validations/` as the single source of truth (DTOs have been removed).
- Every form uses React Hook Form + `zodResolver` + shadcn/ui Form components.
- Use `Control<T>` (e.g. `Control<CompanyForm>`) for FormField — never `as any`.
- Follow AIDER-RULES.md strictly: no `!`, no `as any`, hook-first pattern, quality gate on every change.
- Prefer Biome formatting; never use ESLint or Prettier.
- Keep components small, composable, and focused.
- All database operations go through the service layer or Server Actions.
- Zod schemas must be `.strict()`, use `emptyStringToNull` for nullable fields, and align with `supabase.ts` types.